Please see below for feedback for your Mock Interview session.
When did the session take place?
What mock interview questions were covered?
Design an online media gallery (ie google photos)
What did the student do well?
What should the student work on for their next session or interview?
- Focus more on the core functionalities first
- Try to refer back to the non-functional requirements
- Data models and APIs are crucial and make sure you outline them and explain how they are used/related to the other components
- Don't be afraid to admit you are not familiar with certain part of the feature. The interviewer is more than happy to help you out on smaller details.
- Image size is usually in the KBs
- You didn’t really talk about if you are storing original sized media or transcoded/resized media and how this affects the end user client
- What happens if you are uploading a duplication? How would the service handle it? Would you just repeatedly upload the same file over and over again?
- You don’t really refer back to your earlier nonfunctional-reqs or the traffic estimates
- Try to breakdown the flow into sub-tasks/flow to better explain how each flow for the core component works
- Explain a bit more into the reasoning of why you do certain things. For example, why partition by user_id instead of media_id/url or other field?
- Downloading path - maybe consider using a CDN? It's a common caching mechanism to deliver content fast based on the client's region
- How does the gallery cache know what images to keep in the cache?
